= UrbPed

S3Sol Rails Web app for modeling urban pedestrian walkability.

== Diagrams
To generate diagrams of the models and controllers (using Railroad) type:

    rake doc:diagrams
    
In order to do this, you need to have already installed [Graphviz](http://www.graphviz.org/) on your system.

== Dependencies
* Redis
* Node.js and npm
* Juggernaut npm

* Python 2.7
  pip install networkx
  pip install PyYAML
  sudo apt-get install python-mysqldb
  
* god:
  sudo apt-get install god
  for init script, see http://openmonkey.com/2008/05/27/god-init-script-for-debian-ubuntu-systems/

* pyqt (is required for capybara-webkit, which is used for testing)
	sudo brew install pyqt
  
  
== Install
change config.juggernaut_host in config/environments/production.rb

